<subSubSection id="83F096742CF127CDE210B3A30B24A535" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="comments">
<paragraph id="95E5A2148039AD420B61C77CFD6D208E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F13F8F80F47EDD166C824A80B1487DFA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="715F2EF4C6E84331D2DC759EDA87C517" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia simplex" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="A298098C76B87691FE50162A6B6BA753" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the few 
<taxonomicName id="C7F4228E8F647325783E232D825AD7C7" authorityName="Braschnikov" authorityYear="1897" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5B8199FE1F111CBA229CE67E91A95288" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with an anteriorly recessed gena, a strongly shiny and pronounced fronto-orbital plate and parafacial, a costa that extends only slightly past R4+5, a basiphallus composed of one pair of twisted bands and a bell-shaped distiphallus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18375352A183ECEB64D28F9198920747" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species was transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="0D71FD4962818F86D176E30AD0679B0A" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Hexomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hexomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AD0685EBFC0CAC07CB051533814E270" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hexomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="D42E248AA9D8572B365DB060D9214930" author="von Tschirnhaus, M" editor="Ziegler, J" journalOrPublisher="Nova Supplementa Entomologica, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="113 - 149" refId="B284" refString="von Tschirnhaus, M, 2000. Agromyzidae. In: Ziegler, J, Menzel, F, Eds., Die historische Dipteren-Sammlung Carl Friedrich Ketel. Revision einer zwischen 1884 und 1903 angelegten Sammlung von Zweiflugen (Diptera) aus Mecklenburg-Vorpommern. Nova Supplementa Entomologica, Berlin 14: 113 - 149" title="Agromyzidae." volume="14" volumeTitle="Die historische Dipteren-Sammlung Carl Friedrich Ketel. Revision einer zwischen 1884 und 1903 angelegten Sammlung von Zweiflugen (Diptera) aus Mecklenburg-Vorpommern." year="2000">von Tschirnhaus (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, which was rejected by Zlobin (2005), but again considered 
<taxonomicName id="A2D39C0EC769F9820074D7AA2B83E592" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Hexomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hexomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0FF501AEF9B23EF90A70671922EAC7BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hexomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Papp and Czerny (2015). The boundaries and definition of 
<taxonomicName id="647E82D8125DBC7C27EBAFBBD34D9EFF" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Hexomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hexomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4D068742D5BA92F3DDDC80E29492375C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hexomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered by 
<bibRefCitation id="A3DB3E78D0064515CBB7B11C3292E431" DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/tce.2014.2" author="Lonsdale, O" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="481 - 513" refId="B140" refString="Lonsdale, O, 2014. Redefinition and synonymy of genera in the Ophiomyia genus group, with the description of Euhexomyza new genus (Diptera: Agromyzidae). The Canadian Entomologist 146 (5): 481 - 513, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/tce.2014.2" title="Redefinition and synonymy of genera in the Ophiomyia genus group, with the description of Euhexomyza new genus (Diptera: Agromyzidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/tce.2014.2" volume="146" year="2014">Lonsdale (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, who found the genus to be polyphyletic and the type species embedded within 
<taxonomicName id="3C724E676FF5D86A73DA41F654924874" authorityName="Braschnikov" authorityYear="1897" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A272087C432A759E0D62C379F432AC7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; as a result, 
<taxonomicName id="56531A6EA7B15D107AFA1EA2D1A3B5FC" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Hexomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hexomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="20325D5A8D360F9E16EEEE18CD6B2C75" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hexomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was subsequently included as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="B00996910BA260E78D731492CDC2364B" authorityName="Braschnikov" authorityYear="1897" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="85DC9784B98591EE17B6F965AE4AFE08" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="BB54AB76FBB8594E997A6B71EBF3CBCD" authority="Lonsdale, 2014" authorityName="Lonsdale" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Euhexomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euhexomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5C813056A68924FC196067567108A04E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Euhexomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lonsdale was erected for the remaining related orphaned species. 
<taxonomicName id="B29151765B5847B2C454AA36FBC98F2E" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia simplex" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="E5AF7736AE89C9C366D752D109B73E3A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to share none of the defining characters of 
<taxonomicName id="17BD80ED8C1B0289687C37D5C8312C10" authority="Lonsdale, 2014" authorityName="Lonsdale" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Euhexomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euhexomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DE09B7C4981FA6D7044A6F4F1603424E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Euhexomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except for the high lunule, pronounced orbital plate and parafacial and smaller posteriormost intra-alar, which commonly occur throughout the genus group, including 
<taxonomicName id="2BD72272503A196CEBAB4483769843BE" authorityName="Braschnikov" authorityYear="1897" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="86ED3459D8EB568BB84707F9BBD0365B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There are no convincing adult or larval characters that would ally this stem miner with the gall-forming species previously considered 
<taxonomicName id="072DBA2A9B2416E73718A979F7FEE558" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Hexomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hexomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8E00BA60D302C4B9DC87E26AAF0204E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hexomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially among the highly dissimilar male genitalia.
